'''Apache Samza''' is an [[Open-source software|open-source]] near-realtime, asynchronous computational framework for stream processing developed by the [[Apache Software Foundation]] in [[Scala (programming language)|Scala]] and [[Java (programming language)|Java]].
==History== Apache Samza has been developed in conjunction with [[Apache Kafka]]. Both were originally developed by [[LinkedIn]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.infoq.com/articles/linkedin-samza|title=How LinkedIn Uses Apache Samza|website=InfoQ|access-date=2016-09-28}}</ref>
