{{BLP sources|date=March 2011}} '''Richard Alan Cross''' is Rev. John A. O'Brien Professor of Philosophy and Chair of the Philosophy Department at the [[University of Notre Dame]].<ref>{{Cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | coauthors = | title = Department of Philosophy | work = | publisher = University of Notre Dame | date = | url = http://philosophy.nd.edu/people/all/profiles/cross-richard/index.shtml | doi = | accessdate = 23 December 2010}}</ref> Educated at [[Solihull School]], Cross was formerly Professor of Medieval Theology at the [[University of Oxford]] and Tutor in Theology at [[Oriel College, Oxford]], and holds a [[Master of Arts]] degree and a [[Doctor of Philosophy]] degree. His research interests lie in medieval theology and philosophy, especially [[Duns Scotus]]; [[Christology]] and the [[philosophy of religion]].
Cross is married to Essaka Joshua, a graduate of the universities of Oxford and Birmingham and a specialist in English literature of the Romantic period.
